<title>USA: RailAmerica Inc Q4 full results.</title>
<headline>RailAmerica Inc Q4 full results.</headline>
<dateline>BOCA RATON, Fla. 1997-03-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>RAILAMERICA INC  FINANCIAL HIGHLIGHTS</p>
<p>					    Fiscal Year Ended Dec. 31,</p>
<p>							1996	1995 (a)</p>
<p> Revenue				   $25,658,241   $25,078,104</p>
<p> Depreciation and Amortization	 1,526,510     1,231,622</p>
<p> Interest Expense			  2,078,383     1,277,837</p>
<p> Provision for Income Taxes		705,405	 950,299</p>
<p> Income from Continuing Operations   1,080,437     1,126,243</p>
<p>Per Share Income from</p>
<p>  Continuing Operations			 0.22	    0.10</p>
<p>Loss from Discontinued</p>
<p>  Operations (b)			   (575,558)     (257,910)</p>
<p> Net Income				    504,879	 868,333</p>
<p>Non-Recurring Preferred</p>
<p>  Stock Dividend				    --	 666,665</p>
<p>Net Income Per Share after</p>
<p>  Preferred Stock Dividend		    0.10	    0.04</p>
<p>Wtd. Avg. Common Shares and</p>
<p>  Common Share Equivalents	     4,966,296     4,554,285</p>
<p>					     Consolidated Balance Sheet</p>
<p>						     Dec. 31,</p>
<p>							1996	   1995</p>
<p> Working Capital			  $5,083,342    $3,040,661</p>
<p> Total Assets			     71,564,788    40,063,962</p>
<p> Subordinated Debt			 3,690,274     5,569,331</p>
<p> Stockholders' Equity		   15,992,107     9,148,659</p>
<p> Common Shares Outstanding	     5,888,410     4,658,991</p>
<p>See notes to Consolidated Financial Statements (a)  In the fourth quarter of 1995, the company redeemed</p>
<p>$1 million in face value of convertible preferred stock,</p>
<p>resulting in a non-recurring deemed dividend which</p>
<p>reduced net income available to common shareholders by</p>
<p>$666,665 or $0.14 per share. (b)  In March 1997, the company adopted a plan to discontinue</p>
<p>its motor carrier segment.  The motor carrier segment's</p>
<p>loss reduced net income $575,558, or $.12 per share, in</p>
<p>1996 and $257,910, or $.06 per share, in 1995.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610</p>
